LB62 LB62
2025 2025
1 Section 1. (1) There is hereby appropriated $19,000,000 from the
2 General Fund for FY2025-26 to the Department of Administrative Services,
3 for Program 245, for the purposes described in subsection (2) of this
4 section.
5 (2) The Department of Administrative Services shall provide the
6 funds appropriated in this section to the office of the Chief Information
7 Officer for the following purposes:
8 (a) Establishing interoperable communications between state agencies
9 and volunteer departments by providing portable and mobile radios,
10 programming, and installation of all radios and equipment; and
11 (b) Training for interoperability with the Statewide Radio System to
12 connect volunteer departments and agencies to the Statewide Radio System
13 through a grant program. Eligibility for such program shall be based on
14 the number and type of radios required for each volunteer department
15 based upon such department's needs and size. The office of the Chief
16 Information Officer shall not charge any subscription, programming, or
17 training fee for any volunteer department connected to the Statewide
18 Radio System after receiving a grant from the program. It is the intent
19 of the Legislature that all grant funds be distributed by June 30, 2028.
20 (3) For purposes of this section, volunteer department has the same
21 meaning as in section 35-901.
22 Sec. 2. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
23 passed and approved according to law.
